Interface Summary
IColorDepth
A class implements IColorDepth to indicate that it can change colors of the page data while rendering the page.
IDocumentServer This interface represents a document server that has been defined in the Regini profile.
IDocumentServerFactory A class implements IDocumentServerFactory to indicate that it can create, delete, and return lists of IDocumentServer objects.
IEnhancedSearchTopicItemResult A class implements IEnhancedSearchTopicItemResult to indicate that it is a result of a EnhancedSearchTopicItemFactory createList call.
IFilterResult A IFilterResult interface contains methods to represent a list of matched fields within a single page of a document.
IGrayScale A class implements IGrayScale to indicate that it can change the page data to grayscale while rendering the page.
IHasDescription A class implements IHasDescription to indicate that it has a description.
IHasFieldInfo An interface which gives a search field information.
IHasName A class implements IHasName to indicate that it has a name.
IHasPosition This interface is used to give a filter result position.
IHasProfileLocation A class implements IHasProfileLocation to indicate that it has profile location information.
IHasSectionInfo A class implements IHasSectionInfo to indicate that it can determine a fully qualified Section name.
IHasSession A class implements IHasSession to indicate that it has a session object.
IHasTopicItemEntryInfo A class implements IHasTopicItemEntryInfo to indicate that it has information defining a topic item entry.
IHavePageNotes A page node class, such as ReportPageNode or SearchTopicItemNode, implements IHavePageNotes to indicate that it supports methods for manipulating PageNotes.
IHLLAPIDocumentServer A class implements IHLLAPIDocumentServer to indicate that it has the properties of a HLLAPI document server.
IJPEGParameters A class implements IJPEGParameters to indicate that it can render the page in JPEG format and it can use the quality factor and the passes setting while rendering the page.
IListFactory A class implements IListFactory to indicate it can create INode items.
INeedViewObserver A class implements INeedViewObserver to indicate that it can notify the IViewObserver object when a render setting for the page view has changed.
INode A class implements INode to indicate it is a node in a list.
IPage A class implements IPage to indicate that it is both a page object and a page view factory.
IPageFactory A page node class, such as ReportPageNode or SearchTopicItemNode, implements IPageFactory to indicate that it can create an IPage object.
IPageList This interface when implemented maintains a page list within a class.
IPageNote A class implements IPageNote to indicate that it contains a PageNote.
IPageView A class implements IPageView to indicate that it is a page view object.
IPageViewFactory A page class implements IPageViewFactory to indicate that it is a page object and it can create views on that page.
IRemoteDocumentServer A class implements IRemoteDocumentServer to indicate that it has the properties of a remote document server.
IRenderSubPage A class implements IRenderSubPage to indicate that it can render a sub-page of a page object.
IRenderUsingPolicy A class implements IRenderUsingPolicy to indicate that it can render the page data using the policy information provided.
IResize A class implements IResize to indicate that it can resize and render the page.
IResolution A class implements IResolution to indicate that it can use a resolution in DPI when rendering the page.
IRotate A class implements IRotate to indicate that it can rotate and render the page.
IScale A class implements IScale to indicate that it can scale and render the page.
ISearchTopicItemResult A class implements ISearchTopicItemResult to indicate that it is a result of a SearchTopicItemFactory GetList call.
ISession A class implements ISession to indicate it can create a connection with one or more document servers.
IStreamPage An object which implements IStreamPage can write an arbitrarily large binary object to an output stream.
ISuppressPDFToolbar A class implements ISuppressPDFToolbar to indicate that it can suppress Adobe Toolbars when converting documents to PDF.
ITCPIPDocumentServer A class implements ITCPIPDocumentServer to indicate that it has the properties of a TCP/IP document server.
IUsesExternalProduct A class implements IUsesExternalProduct to indicate that it requires an external product to run.
IVersion A class implements IVersion to indicate it has the state of a Version ID.
IViewObserver A class implements IViewObserver to indicate that it needs to be notified when the render settings for a page view has changed.
PageClass Defines IDs for all known page classes

TopicVersionNode A TopicVersionNode object is created by a Topic object, and represents a version of a topic located on a specified document server.
Types The Types class contains values that specify sizes and limits applying to the ViewDirect Java API.
VdrSearchExpression Enhanced Topic Item searches are built in terms of VdrSearchExpression objects which consist of VdrSearchTerm object(s) joined by an OR or AND SearchConjunction operator.
VdrSearchTerm The VdrSearchTerm abstract class is the base class of search terms used by the VdrSearchExpression class.
VersionDateTimeFormatter A class uses a VersionDateTimeFormatter object to convert a version string formatted in a 'user-friendly' date-time format into the default date-time string version ID formatted as YYYYMMDDHHMMSS.
VersionFieldType Enumerates the different fields of a Version ID, and is used for parsing Version IDs so they can be reformatted.
VersionIdFormatter A class uses a VersionIdFormatter object to convert a version ID, which is by default rendered as a time-date string in the format YYYYMMDDHHMMSS, into a more 'user-friendly' format.
VersionNode This abstract class implements common functions for IVersion objects.
VersionResultColumn A VersionResultColumn object defines a Version column (and its sort order) to be returned from an enhanced search topic item query.
VersionSearchTerm This class represents a VersionID search term (or search constraint) used within a VdrSearchExpression.
ViewDirectSeverityLevel This class defines the severity of events that can occur during the execution of API functions, and is used to indicate the level of trace output.
